      • setNavigationShown

        public void setNavigationShown(boolean isShown)
        Description copied from class: NavigableActivity
        Handles visibility of this screen's navigation menu. This could be a bottom navigation, tabs, a drawer or any other custom implementation.

        Keep in mind that this method does not provide a default implementation, as there isn't a single global navigation menu for the entire app. Override it as needed.
        Overrides:
        setNavigationShown in class NavigableActivity
        Parameters:
        isShown - true to show the navigation menu, false to hide it.

      • getContentResId

        @IdRes
protected int getContentResId()
        Description copied from class: NavigableActivity
        Returns the layout resource ID of the main content placeholder. This is used by methods such as NavigableActivity.setContentFragment(T, com.intel.fightclub.ui.screens.common.object.NavigationSection) and NavigableActivity.pushContentFragment(T, android.support.v4.app.Fragment.SavedState, java.lang.String) to replace fragments that take the entire screen. While the specified fragment is loading, NavigableActivity.getLoadingResId() will be visible instead.
        Specified by:
        getContentResId in class NavigableActivity

      • getLoadingResId

        @IdRes
protected int getLoadingResId()
        Description copied from class: NavigableActivity
        Returns the layout resource ID of the loading placeholder. This is used to display a progress indicator that takes the entire screen, before it's replaced by a loaded fragment. The visibility of this layout is alternated with NavigableActivity.getContentResId(). i.e. it's visible when getContentResId is hidden (while a fragment is being loaded).
        Specified by:
        getLoadingResId in class NavigableActivity
